ar Dame, Tediore || || <ref>{{cite video game | developer=[[2K Australia]], [[Gearbox Software]] | title=[[Borderlands: The Pre-Sequel!]] | publisher=[[2K Games]] | scene=Closing credits, 4:40 in}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2014|format=y}} || ''[[Smite (video game)|Smite]]'' || Hel, Sobek's Parrot || || <ref name=\"btva\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2016|10|25|format=y}} || ''[[Dragon Ball Xenoverse 2]]'' || Bulma || || <ref name=\"btva\"/>\n|- \n| {{dts|2017|01|24|format=y}} || ''[[Tales of Berseria]]'' || Bienfu, Seres || || <ref name=\"btva\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2017|05|19|format=y}} || ''[[Fire Emblem Echoes: Shadows of Valentia]]'' || Mila || || <ref>{{Cite tweet|number=865355402204065794 |title=Now that's it's been released, I can announce that I voice Mila in Fire Emblem Echoes: Shadows of Valentia. | user=rialisms | author=Monica Rial | date=May 18, 2017 | access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2018|01|26|format=y}} || ''[[Dragon Ball FighterZ]]'' || Bulma || || <ref name=\"btva\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2019|02|19|format=y}} || ''Dragon Ball Legends'' || Bulma || || <ref name=\"btva\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2020|01|17|format=y}} || ''[[Dragon Ball Z: Kakarot]]'' || Bulma || || <ref name=\"btva\"/>\n|}\n<!-- NEED SOURCE AND NOTABILITY\n* ''Backstage Pass'' \u2013 Nicole\n| {{dts|2008|01|22|format=y}} || ''[[One Piece: Unlimited Adventure]]'' || Kuina || ||\n| {{dts|2010|10|06|format=y}} || ''[[Comic Jumper: The Adventures of Captain Smiley]]'' || Nana || ||\n-->\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"btva\">{{cite web | url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/monica-rial/ | title=Monica Rial | work=Behind The Voice Actors | date=2019 | accessdate=February 13, 2019}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"latino\">{{cite magazine | last=Doty | first=Terri | authorlink=Terri Doty | issue=6 | page=18 | publication-date=October\u2013November 2013 | url=http://issuu.com/latinoleadersmagazine/docs/llv14n6single | title=Monica Rial | work=Latino Leaders Magazine | volume=14}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"resume\">\nResumes:\n* {{cite web | url=http://www.marycollins.com/monica-rial | title=Monica Rial | work=Mary Collins Talent | accessdate=November 2, 2015 }}\n* {{cite web | url=http://resumes.breakdownexpress.com/772237-2116970 | title=Monica Rial | work=Breakdown Express | accessdate=November 2, 2015 }}\n* {{cite web | url=https://www.nowcasting.com/actor/popup/viewactor.php?actorID=mrial&defaultImage=1 | title=Monica Rial | work=Now Casting | accessdate=November 2, 2015 }}\n* {{cite web | url=http://cni.castingnetworks.com/talent/profile/435848?rs=1&crypt=dicgliaifpggfglfgbdhdnafhjmakdfaianlbopipkmcfehm | title=Monica Rial | work=Casting Networks | accessdate=November 2, 2015}}\n</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{AnimeCons name|id=641|name=Monica Rial}}\n* {{ann|people|id=2074|name=Monica Rial}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0722676|name=Monica Rial}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rial, Monica}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American people of Spanish descent]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Houston]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Dallas]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American video game actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:American women screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American actresses]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American writers]]\n[[Category:People from Houston]]\n[[Category:People from Dallas]]\n[[Category:University of Houston alumni]]\n[[Category:Voice directors]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from Texas]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American voice actress}}\n{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Monica Rial\n| image              = Monica Rial GalaxyCon Richmond 2020.jpg\n| caption            = Rial at GalaxyCon Richmond in 2020\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1975|10|05}}\n| birth_place        = [[Houston]], [[Texas]], U.S.<!-- birthplace confirmed by connected contributor Hellomonichan -->\n| residence          = [[Dallas]], Texas, U.S.<ref name=\"observer\"/><br />Houston, Texas, U.S.<!-- listed on her Twitter account as of November 3, 2015-->\n| alma_mater         = [[University of Houston]]<ref name=\"resume\"/>\n| occupation         = Voice actress, ADR director, script writer\n| years_active       = 1999\u2013present\n| agent              = Mary Collins Agency\n| spouse             = \n| partner            = \n| children           = \n| relatives          = Natalie Rial (sister)<ref name=\"natalie\">{{Cite tweet|number=396448214280196096 |title=Yes, you read the Girls Und Panzer cast list correctly. Natalie Rial is my little sister. The Rials are taking over the anime world. \ud83d\ude1c | user=rialisms | author=Monica Rial | date=November 1, 2013 | access-date=2017-05-26 }}</ref><br>Miguel Rial (brother)\n| birthname          = Monica Jean Rial\n| alias              = <!-- NEED SOURCE Dorothy Garrett, Lisa Blanchard -->\n| url                = {{URL|themonicarial.com}}\n}}\n'''Monica Jean Rial''' (born October 5, 1975)<ref>{{cite tweet | title=It's my birthday Monday! All I want is for you to watch #MichikoAndHatchin tonight!!!! | date=October 3, 2015 | user=Rialisms | author=Monica Rial | number=650544004615012352 | accessdate=November 3, 2015}}</ref><!-- year confirmed by connected contributor Hellomonichan -->  is an American voice actress, [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|ADR director]] and [[screenwriter|script writer]] affiliated with [[Funimation]] and [[Seraphim Digital]]/[[Sentai Filmworks]]. She provides voices for English language versions of Japanese [[anime]] films and television series.\n\n==Early life==\nMonica Jean Rial was born on October 5, 1975 in [[Houston, Texas]]. Her father is from [[Pontevedra]], Galicia, Spain. When she was young, her family would often visit Spain. She would translate for her younger brother some of the European Spanish-dubbed cartoons which included anime shows ''[[Doraemon]]'' and ''[[Dragon Ball Z]]'', often imitating the various characters.<ref name=\"latino\"/><ref name=\"observer\"/> Rial studied ballet, tap, and jazz, but transitioned to musical theater when was 12.<ref name=\"otakunews 2006\">{{cite web|url=http://www.otakunews.com/article.php?story=952|title=Otaku News : Interview with Monica Rial and Chris Patton|first=Rebecca |last=McCarthy|date=September 21, 2006|work=Otaku News|accessdate=November 3, 2015}}</ref> She studied acting through high school as well as college at the [[University of Houston]].<ref name=\"resume\"/><ref name=\"observer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dallasobserver.com/arts/the-fun-factory-inside-funimation-the-anime-dubbing-powerhouse-thats-keeping-dallas-actors-in-work-8095737|title=The Fun Factory: Inside Funimation, the Anime-Dubbing Powerhouse That's Keeping Dallas Actors in Work|first=Caroline|last=North|date=March 8, 2016|work=[[The Dallas Observer]]|accessdate=July 18, 2016}}</ref> In an interview with Otaku News, Rial mentioned voice actor inspirations from ''[[The Simpsons]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'' and ''[[Beavis and Butt-head]]''.<ref name=\"otakunews 2006\"/> She was working on a theater show with [[Jason Douglas]], who suggested she audition for [[ADV Films]].\n\n==Career==\nRial's first voice-over role was some [[walla]] in the 1999 dub of ''[[Martian Successor Nadesico]]''. In an interview with Otaku News, Rial said she had to talk for two minutes straight as folks in a crowd telling the Jovians to go home.<ref name=\"otakunews 2006\"/> She would later land main character roles as Miharu in ''[[Gasaraki]]'', Natsume in ''[[Generator Gawl]]'', and the title character in ADV Films' production of ''[[Hello Kitty (TV series)|Hello Kitty's Animation Theater]]'',<ref name=\"diehard\"/><ref name=\"otakunews\"/> the last of which was one of ADV's best-selling DVDs.<ref name=\"activeanime 2006\"/> In 2001, she voiced Izumi in the baseball anime ''[[Princess Nine]]'' and in 2002, she got to voice Hyatt in ''[[Excel Saga]]'', which she listed among her absolute favorites.<ref name=\"diehard\"/>\n\nIn 2003, Rial voiced best-friend character [[List of Full Metal Panic characters#Kyoko Tokiwa|Kyoko Tokiwa]] in ''[[Full Metal Panic!]]'', and got to reprise her for ''Full Metal Panic? Fumoffu'' and ''Full Metal Panic: The Second Raid''. In the same year, Rial voiced Kirika Yumura, the quiet assassin partner in ''[[Noir (anime)|Noir]]''. Rial said that Kirika was challenging because she had very few words but had to convey a lot of emotions.<ref name=\"diehard\"/> She also noted that Kirika's personality changed over the course of the series, so she voiced her to be more emotional in later episodes which drew some criticism from fans. She also voiced Lila in ''[[Najica Blitz Tactics]]'' where she also got to do a DVD commentary along with fellow actress [[Kira Vincent-Davis]]. The commentaries have become popular as she receives feedback from fans about them at anime conventions.<ref name=\"otakunews\">{{cite web|url=http://www.otakunews.com/us/article.php?story=68|title=Otaku News : An Interview With Monica Rial|first=Rebecca|last=McCarthy|date=September 8, 2004|work=Otaku News|accessdate=November 3, 2015}}</ref> She voiced female protagonist [[List of RahXephon characters#Haruka Shitou|Haruka Shitou]] in the sci-fi show ''[[RahXephon]]''.\n\nIn 2004, Rial started voice-over work with the anime dubbing company [[Funimation]] in the Dallas/Ft. Worth area. During that year, she voiced [[List of Case Closed characters#Amy Yoshida|Amy]] in the long-running detective anime series ''[[Case Closed (manga)|Case Closed]]'', and [[List of Fullmetal Alchemist characters#Lyra|Lyra]] (aka Dante) in the drama series ''[[Fullmetal Alchemist]]''. Both of these shows were featured on Cartoon Network. She also voiced co-lead character Lumiere in ''[[Kiddy Grade]]''.<ref name=\"ann 20040911\"/> Meanwhile, with ADV, she voiced [[List of Azumanga Daioh characters#Nyamo|Nyamo-sensei]] in the school comedy ''[[Azumanga Daioh]]''. She had also taken over some character roles as Momiji in ''[[Blue Seed]]'' and Maya in ''[[Neon Genesis Evangelion]]''. Rial said that it was very difficult to try to sound like the previous voice actors, especially Maya's low voice, so she tried her own approach. She also got to voice Pen-Pen the penguin in ''Evangelion''.<ref name=\"ann 20040513\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2004-05-13/2|title=Interview: Colleen Clinkenbeard and Monica Rial|first=Chris|last=Fey|date=May 13, 2004|work=Anime News Network|accessdate=November 11, 2015}}</ref> In 2005, she voiced the serious lead character Jo in a team of mercenary girls in the cyberpunk science fiction series ''[[Burst Angel]]''.<ref name=\"burst angel review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/30653/burst-angel-deaths-angel-v1/|title=Burst Angel \u2013 Death's Angel v.1|first=Don|last=Houston|date=September 24, 2007|work=DVD Talk|accessdate=November 3, 2015}}</ref>\n\nRial continued to land leading roles in anime shows. In 2006, she voiced the title character in ''[[Nanaka 6/17]]'', about a 17-year-old girl who, through an accident, has amnesia and regresses to her 6-year-old self. In ''[[Speed Grapher]]'' she voiced female protagonist [[List of Speed Grapher characters#Kagura Tenn\u014dzu|Kagura Tenn\u014dzu]], and in the ADV Films remake of ''[[The Super Dimension Fortress Macross|Macross]]'', she voiced [[Misa Hayase]].<ref name=\"activeanime 2006\"/> In 2007, she voiced [[Sakura (Tsubasa: Reservoir Chronicle)|Sakura]] in the English anime adaptation of Clamp's ''[[Tsubasa: Reservoir Chronicle]]''; Maria in ''[[Witchblade (anime)|Witchblade]]'';<ref name=\"marchi 20131010\"/> Misuzu Kamio, a heroine in ''[[Air (TV series)|Air]]'', and the title character in ''[[Kurau: Phantom Memory]]''.  She also voiced lead characters Misao Shinohara, Sasami's best friend in ''[[Sasami: Magical Girls Club]]''; and heroine [[Asa Shigure]] in the harem comedy ''[[Shuffle!]]''.\n\n[[File:2017 Wizard World Columbus - Monica Rial (36039256730).jpg|thumb|Rial at Wizard World Columbus in 2017]]\n\nIn 2010, when ''[[Dragon Ball Z]]'' was remade as ''Dragon Ball Z Kai'', Rial got to voice the heroine character [[Bulma]]. She voiced other lead girl characters such as Miya Asami in ''[[Sekirei]]'', [[Tsubaki Nakatsukasa]] in ''[[Soul Eater (manga)|Soul Eater]]'', May Chang in ''[[Fullmetal Alchemist Brotherhood]]'', and Ringo in ''[[Casshern Sins]]''. Both ''Soul Eater'' and ''Fullmetal Alchemist Brotherhood'' have had sizeable runs on [[Adult Swim]]'s [[Toonami]] block. In 2011, she voiced the title character Mina Tepes in ''[[Dance in the Vampire Bund]]'', as well as several lead female characters in ensemble shows ''[[Rosario + Vampire]]'', ''[[Highschool of the Dead]]'' and ''[[Fairy Tail]]'', such as Yukari Sendou, [[Shizuka Marikawa]], and Mirajane Strauss respectively.\n\nRial voiced more leads in 2012 with [[List of Deadman Wonderland characters#Shiro|Shiro]] in ''[[Deadman Wonderland]]'' which also broadcast on [[Adult Swim]], Stocking in the raunchy comedy ''[[Panty & Stocking with Garterbelt]]''. In 2013, she voiced the heroine character Haruko Amaya in the harem comedy ''[[Maken-ki!]]'' and Iori Nagase in the school anime series ''[[Kokoro Connect]]''. With regards to her lead role of Michiko Malandro in ''[[Michiko & Hatchin]]'', which was released on DVD in 2013 and was broadcast on [[Adult Swim]] in 2015, Rial said that out of the 300 or so characters she had voiced, only two of them were Hispanic, and she liked that her character wasn't a stereotype.<ref name=\"latino\"/> In 2014 and 2015, she voiced the title characters in the comedies ''[[Watamote]]'' and ''[[Maid Sama!]]'' as Tomoko Kuroki and Misaki Ayuzawa, respectively. <!-- more can be written about her recent works -->\n\nIn addition to voice acting, Rial has been steadily involved in ADR script writing, with work in the English dubs for ''[[D.N. Angel]]'', ''[[Madlax]]'', and ''[[Gatchaman]]''. In an interview with Active Anime, Rial said she would \"take the direct translation and write it into a coherent scene that matches the lip flaps\".<ref name=\"activeanime 2006\">{{cite web|url=http://activeanime.com/html/2006/01/09/monica-rial/|title=\u00bb MONICA RIAL|author=|date=January 9, 2006|work=ActiveAnime|accessdate=November 3, 2015}}</ref> At later anime conventions, Rial has mentioned that ADR script writing has kept her quite occupied, especially with [[Funimation#Simuldub program|simuldubs]], which are shows that are locally dubbed soon after the original broadcast. She has also written columns for ''[[Newtype]]''{{'}}s USA edition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aintitcool.com/node/33522|title=AICN Anime \u2013 A Survey of Print Resources|last=Green|first=Scott|date=August 1, 2007|work=Aint It Cool News|accessdate=November 3, 2015}}</ref> In January 2018, Rial has announced that she is taking time off of script adaptation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Rialisms/status/950510647514730496|title=Just to clarify, when I said I was taking some time off I meant from script adapting. I\u2019m still voice acting! That\u2019s my passion!|last=Rial|first=Monica|date=2018-01-08|website=@Rialisms|language=en|access-date=2019-02-06}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Rial alleged that she had been sexually assaulted by fellow voice actor [[Vic Mignogna]] in 2007.<ref name=\"ann 2019-02-20\">{{cite news|author=Rafael Antonio Pineda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-02-20/bulma-voice-actress-monica-rial-shares-alleged-inappropriate-encounters-with-vic-mignogna/.143664|title=Bulma Voice Actress Monica Rial Shares Alleged Inappropriate Encounters With Vic Mignogna|work=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2019-02-20|accessdate=2019-02-20}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Mignogna filed a lawsuit against Rial, her fianc\u00e9, Ron Toye, as well as Funimation and [[Jamie Marchi]] for tortious interference, civil conspiracy, and defamation in regards to Rial's allegations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-04-19/vic-mignogna-sues-funimation-jamie-marchi-monica-rial-ronald-toye/.145898|title=Vic Mignogna Sues Funimation, Jamie Marchi, Monica Rial, Ronald Toye|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref> On July 19, 2019, Rial, Toye and Marchi all filed [[Strategic lawsuit against public participation|anti-SLAPP]] motions for Mignogna to dismiss his lawsuit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-22/monica-rial-ronald-toye-jamie-marchi-also-file-motions-to-dismiss-vic-mignogna-lawsuit/.149217|title=Monica Rial, Ronald Toye, Jamie Marchi Also File Motions to Dismiss Vic Mignogna's Lawsuit|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-08-09}}</ref> On October 4, 2019, the case was dismissed, and all the charges against Funimation, Marchi, Rial and Toye were dropped.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mateo |first1=Alex |title=Vic Mignogna's Civil Case Against Funimation, Voice Actress Monica Rial, Ron Toye Dismissed |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-04/vic-mignogna-civil-case-against-funimation-voice-actress-monica-rial-ron-toye-dismissed/.151881 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=October 5, 2019 |date=October 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nRial has a younger brother, Miguel, and a younger sister, Natalie, who is also an actress. Both siblings have voiced in anime dubs.<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=307503149629964289|title=In other news, it's my little bro Miguel Rial's bday! He was in FMA ep 27 as \"Boy with the broken train\"! Happy 29, Guels! #MylilBroRocks!|last=Rial|first=Monica|date=2013-03-01|user=Rialisms|access-date=2019-02-07}}</ref><ref name=\"natalie\"/> Rial is currently engaged to Ron Toye.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1118589196367740931|user=Rialisms|first=Monica|last=Rial|date= April 17, 2019|title=@RonToye is my fianc\u00e9. Our life is pretty weird already. That said, I welcome more weirdness.}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Anime===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of voice performances and production work in anime\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Crew role, Notes <!-- place crew roles here -->\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Source<ref name=\"resume\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|1999}} || ''[[Martian Successor Nadesico]]'' || Mikako, Miss Kobayashi || Debut roles || <ref name=\"diehard\"/><ref name=\"otakunews 2006\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2000}} || ''[[Hello Kitty (TV series)|Hello Kitty's Animation Theater]]'' || Hello Kitty || ADV and Sanrio production || Press<ref name=\"activeanime 2006\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2000}} || ''[[Gasaraki]]'' || Miharu || || <ref name=\"diehard\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2000}} || ''[[Generator Gawl]]'' || [[Generator Gawl#Natsume|Natsume]] || <!-- ADV episode credits --> || <ref name=\"diehard\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2001}} || ''[[Princess Nine]]'' || [[Princess Nine#Izumi Himuro|Izumi Himuro]] || <!-- ADV episode credits --> || <ref name=\"diehard\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/princess-nine/dvd-complete-collection/.75038|title=Princess Nine DVD Complete Series|author=|date=|website=animenewsnetwork.com|accessdate=August 17, 2018}}</ref><!-- Hilary Haag, Monica Rial, and a heap of other ADV old guard shine with enthusiasm, chemistry, and a freedom to express themselves through sincere emotion without the constraints of maintaining the more modernly enforced \"anime girl voice.\" -->\n|-\n| {{dts|2002}} || ''[[Excel Saga]]'' || [[Hyatt (Excel Saga)|Hyatt]] || || <ref name=\"diehard\">{{cite web|url=http://diehardgamefan.com/2014/03/20/evillecon-2014-interview-with-voice-actress-monica-rial/ |title=EvilleCon 2014: Interview with Voice Actress Monica Rial |work=Diehard Gamefan |date=March 26, 2014 |accessdate=June 26, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"my voice acting uk interview 2006\"/><ref>