 Hurricanes To Come\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.livescience.com/environment/050831_hurricane_freq.html |title=Many More Hurricanes To Come |last=Than |first=Ker |date=August 31, 2005 |publisher=[[Imaginova|Live Science]] |accessdate=2007-12-03 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070714035204/http://www.livescience.com/environment/050831_hurricane_freq.html |archivedate=2007-07-14 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"More earthquakes than usual? Not really.\">{{Cite news|first=Margaret Webb|last=Presler|title=More earthquakes than usual? Not really|url=|work=Washington Post| location=Washington D.C.|pages= C10|date=14 April 2010|id=|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NOAA Attributes Recent Increase In Hurricane Activity To Naturally Occurring Multi-Decadal Climate Variability\">{{cite web |url=http://www.magazine.noaa.gov/stories/mag184.htm |title=NOAA Attributes Recent Increase In Hurricane Activity To Naturally Occurring Multi-Decadal Climate Variability |publisher=[[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]] |accessdate=2007-12-03 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051203220222/http://www.magazine.noaa.gov/stories/mag184.htm |archivedate=2005-12-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NOAA\u2019s misleading internal Congressional briefing points on hurricanes and global warming\">{{cite web|url=http://www.climatesciencewatch.org/2006/05/31/noaas-misleading-internal-congressional-briefing-points-on-hurricanes-and-global-warming/ |title=NOAA's misleading internal Congressional briefing points on hurricanes and global warming |publisher=Climate Science Watch |accessdate=2012-11-26}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Hurricane Science Becomes a Matter of Policy as NOAA Takes Sides\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ucsusa.org/scientific_integrity/abuses_of_science/hurricane-science-becomes-a.html |title=Hurricane Science Becomes a Matter of Policy as NOAA Takes Sides |publisher=Union of Concerned Scientists |accessdate=2012-11-26}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Not al